(book-manifest
  :book             "Book of Sick Composition"
  :short-name       "book-of-sick-composition"
  :chapter-count    8
  :audience         "kid-and-adult operators, Motoi copilot"
  :dialect          "motoi"
  :voice            "motoi-copilot"
  :training-eligible #t
  :confidentiality  "public"
  :date-created     "2026-07-18"
  :provenance
    ((:authored-at "2026-07-18"
      :authored-by "ada composition-density lane (motoi-3.5)"
      :edit-source "MOTOI-3.5-EXECUTION-2026-07-18"
      :sources
        ((:reference "scheme/MOTOI-SCHEME-REFERENCE.slat" :scope "all verbs cited")
         (:book "book-of-composition" :chapter "1-16" :scope "composer round-trip, canvas, widget patterns")
         (:book "book-of-scheme" :chapter "1-16" :scope "base + higher-order + recursion + macros")
         (:book "book-of-motion" :chapter "1-16" :scope "animation, easing, forces, timing")
         (:book "book-of-music" :chapter "1-16" :scope "notes, synth, orchestra")
         (:doctrine "project_no_contaminants_provenance_rule_2026_07_17"
          :scope "no LLM invention; every verb from reference; every problem authored under intent"))))
  :scope
"The Book of Sick Composition is a ramp — easy to pro, one lib per
chapter, every chapter takes Motoi from nothing to something. Each
chapter opens with what the lib is and why it exists, then a stack
of four problems that step up in complexity: draw a circle → draw a
field of circles → make them pulse → make them respond to a click.
Every line of code is a real Motoi verb from the reference. Every
solution is authored under intent — no LLM-invented facts, no
scraped patterns, no pseudo-code.

The book teaches the shape of composition Alfred cares about: the
kid opens the file, tries a thing, sees the thing, then trades one
detail for another and sees the picture change. Nothing-to-something
in the small; nothing-to-a-whole-game by chapter eight."
  :chapters
    ((:number 1 :title "The Base — car, cdr, cons, and the shape of everything")
     (:number 2 :title "Lists You Move Around — map, filter, and the joy of pipes")
     (:number 3 :title "Higher-Order — functions that take functions")
     (:number 4 :title "Recursion Without Fear — the same trick, again and again")
     (:number 5 :title "The Frame — fb, text, and drawing your first picture")
     (:number 6 :title "The World Loop — big-bang, on-tick, to-draw")
     (:number 7 :title "Entities on the Field — world/spawn, entity/*, and the physics you get free")
     (:number 8 :title "Sound and Music — note/strike, synth/chord, and a song from scratch"))
  :composes-with
    ((:doctrine "project_no_contaminants_provenance_rule_2026_07_17")
     (:doctrine "project_motoi_personality_2026_07_17")
     (:doctrine "project_motoi_is_the_new_speak_and_spell_2026_07_17")
     (:doctrine "feedback_stop_fake_completion_cycle_2026_07_16")
     (:book "book-of-composition")
     (:book "book-of-scheme")))
